ed. This book will be a valuable resource for postgraduates and researchers interested in language variation and change, ELF and second language acquisition, as well as for undergraduates wanting guidance on different ways of examining sociolinguistic variables.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aCommunicative competencezSwitzerland. 0aElectronic mail messagesxSocial aspects. 0aInterlanguage (Language learning) 0aInterlanguage (Language learning). 0aLanguage and languagesxVariation. 0aSecond language acquisitionzSwitzerland. 0aSecond language acquisition. 0aSociolinguisticszSwitzerland. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Sociolinguistics.2bisacsh  aELF.  aEnglish as a Lingua Franca.  aLingua Franca.  aSLA.  aSecond Language Acquisition.  aSociolinguistic Competence.  aforeign language learning.  alinguistic variables.  asecond language learning.  asociolinguistics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978178309144740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781783091447423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781783091447/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK